Copyright.AdditionalInfo: Lithoprobe Western Superior Transect MT Broad band magnetotelluric data collected during Lithoprobe project. Tags: Keyword:Earth sciences Keyword:Geophysics Keyword:Magnetism Additional Information Date published September 21, 2000 Keywords Earth sciences, Geophysics, Magnetism, magnetotelluric, lithoprobe, electromagnetic, northern ontario... show more Series Geological Survey of Canada, Seismic and Magnetotelluric Data 171 Issues Lithoprobe WS Transect MT - 22 sites from WS falco 47 sites from WS geo00 11 sites from WS red00 12 sites from WS pickle 158 sites from WS wst98 Author Brian Roberts The data archive is a planned output of the LITHOPROBE project and is meant to be accessible to all Canadians. Regional seismic lines and magnetotelluric sites provide an excellent framework for understanding crustal scale geological features in many important areas of the Country. Licence Open Government Licence - Canada (http://open.canada.ca/en/open-government-licence-canada) Contact Information: Government of Canada; Natural Resources Canada; Earth Sciences Sector; Canada Centre for Mapping and Earth Observation Telephone: 1-819-564-4857 Telephone: 1-800-661-2638 (Toll Free in Canada and USA.) E-mail: NRCan.geogratis-geogratis.RNCan@canada.ca These data were converted from the original EDI SPECTRA format using EMTF FCU 4.0 developed by Anna Kelbert, USGS last updated in Nov 2017. This novel algorithm allows for estimation of full error covariances from cross-power spectra. We thank Xavier Garcia and Gary Egbert for valuable advice that helped develop the spectra conversion algorithm.
